    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 framework. The CFD model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The relative hemolysis index predictions satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all 5 evaluated operating points. The assessment team notes that the hemolysis quantification methodology, including the empirical coefficient selection informing the RH threshold, draws on recent literature (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) that provides updated power-law exponents for shear-induced hemolysis in rotary pumps. The overall credibility package supports regulatory submission.",
